f the trends that would soon ignite controversy, of the arguments they would spawn, of the inevitable backlash lurking just beyond the applause.\n\n(5) When the host finally turned and, for the first time, his eyes met Julian’s, a quiet, terrible understanding passed between them. The man’s expression was unreadable—older, perhaps, carrying"